data.description: Nice quiet neighborhood nestled in with several other beautiful historic homes. Seven short blocks from the Seawall and close to UTMB Medical Center. Home has curb appeal and is very clean and well-maintained. House was built in 1914, so it qualifies for historic designation, if interested. Giant oak trees out front, that are, also, over 100 years old. No water in home from Ike, or any other storm. X flood zone and property is on the highest point of the island. House is very sturdy! Large rooms, beautiful hardwoods and custom woodwork.   Lots of windows. Great party home, with 3 decks including deck off master, which is shaded by a motorized, retractable Sunsetter awning.  Coffered ceiling in kitchen / family room.  Utility closet in kitchen. Many electric outlets. On demand hot water heaters. Double shower master bath is onyx and travertine. Washer and dryer conveniently located upstairs.  Gas fireplace in parlor. Original dual stair way between kitchen and entryway. Seven ceiling fans, central A/C and heat upstairs, minisplits downstairs. Walk-in closet in master bedroom, cedar lined closet in second bedroom, and closet fitted with shelving system in third bedroom. New privacy fences on west side and southeast side. East side has off-street parking and additional off-street parking can be created for more vehicles if desired. Oversized two car detached cinderblock garage opens onto the alley and can be built up to create additional apartment. House has been recently updated with both interior and exterior paint. Wonderful home, with lots of nooks and crannies and many unique and clever touches.
data.whatILove:
The best of the Old World and the new. Charming Victorian Exterior, with beautifully updated interior. 
Wide Open concept Kitchen, Dining, Living room area, very rarely found in Galveston. A 54 second drive to the Beach, or a 9-minute walk. Wide double lot for room to breathe, unlike most cramped Galveston homesites. No water in Ike!
